The paper deals with the design of a receiver for 3D massive MIMO-OFDM systems, which involves joint channel estimation and decoding. This falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of Gaussian message passing and variational expectation-maximization (EM) methods, which are commonly used in statistical inference (cs.SI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with the performance evaluation of the proposed algorithm in 3D massive MIMO systems, which falls under the domain of multimedia (cs.MM).
